It is generally accepted that the split in marriage is a natural process. The main reason for divorce is that many potential partners quarrel about money and when they are facing economic problems, they feel rather disappointed. People do not want to cope with problems in life together, but rather walk away complaining about those.

Courses on marriage

Matrimony in Lithuania is understood by most people as a contract that ultimately should be terminated legally, as the country does not see the need to apply religion and customs to weddings. Hence, young women hold Lithuania’s wedding. People like that because while the civil service is seen as a purely legal act, the Church sees it as religious and as opposed to divorce. The Government has dealt with same-sex marriage and same-sex partnerships so far, although they are included in a range of countries that have legalized same-sex marriage since 2013. As a result, Lithuanian women have questioned their rights because they want to feel empowered and enjoy the rights of men. This is one of the main reasons for these challenges.
